Convert string categorical variable to a numeric variable
def gender(x):
    if x == 'male': return 1
    else: return 0

df['Sex'] = df['Sex'].apply(gender)

def port(x):
    if x == 'C': return 1
    elif x == 'Q': return 2
    else: return 0

df['Embarked'] = df['Embarked'].apply(port)

def name(x):
    count = 0
    for title in (df.Name.unique()):
        if x == title: return count 
        count = count + 1

df['Name'] = df['Name'].apply(name)
